sentences.english: The information acquisition technique of intersected primitive based on combined relationship is provided.
sentences.chinese: 提出了基於形體組合關係的相交基元體信息獲取技術。

sentences.english: Mix with your equals or betters.
sentences.chinese: 與同你相等或比你好的人相交。

sentences.english: My secret communion with God is the place where I learn the great lessons concerning God's will.
sentences.chinese: 在與神相交的隱密處，我學到有關神旨意的偉大功課。

sentences.english: This is the question of fellowship.
The two roads meet north of Goodman.
sentences.chinese: 這兩條路在古德曼以北相交。

sentences.english: Consider a family of parallel lines that cut the conic .
sentences.chinese: 設有一組平行線與圓錐曲線相交。

sentences.english: Any two diameters of a circle intersect each other.
Attached Colliders' objects must intersect with the cloth you are attaching to.
sentences.chinese: 注意，被附着的碰撞體必須與布料有相交。

sentences.english: An intersection formed in this way.
sentences.chinese: 兩條路或街相交的地方。

sentences.english: Serge said his artwork was “all about the intersection of text and space.”
sentences.chinese: Serge說他的藝術品是“相交的文字和空間”。

sentences.english: The cables intersect the tower or pylon at different heights.
sentences.chinese: 鋼索在橋塔或塔柱的不同高度上相交。

sentences.english: The North Pole is the spot on Earth’s globe that marks the northern end of an imaginary stick Earth spins around.
sentences.chinese: 北極是地球表面與假想的自轉軸相交的北交點。

sentences.english: But we, are two parallel lines, can only look, but can not intersect.
sentences.chinese: 而我們，註定是兩條平行線，只能相望，卻不能相交。

sentences.english: There have been many years since Song Ziwen and Zhang Xueliang made friends.
sentences.chinese: 宋子文與張學良相交多年，兩人以兄弟相稱。

sentences.english: Life is full of coincidences, two parallels will intersect one day!
sentences.chinese: 生命中充滿巧合，兩條平行錢也會有相交的一天。

sentences.english: Intersection means the place where drifts intersect at or branch off.
sentences.chinese: 交岔點是指巷道相交或分岔的地點。
